</div>

:: DirectTravelBuyAlone
<<set $step = 0>><<ShowInfo>>

<h3>Solo Purchase</h3>
<div class="consequence-text">
	<p>You decide to buy the car on your own. With your successful premium service business, you can afford it comfortably.</p>
	<p>You find a 2010 Toyota Corolla with 145,000 miles. It's in good condition - well-maintained, clean interior, reliable engine. The seller wants $1,600 cash.</p>
	<p>You pay $1,600 for the car, another $150 for insurance, and $100 for registration. Even after these expenses, you still have money left over from your hard work.</p>
	<p>When you drive it to your first client job, they're impressed. "You have your own car now," one says. "You're really building something."</p>
	<p>And they're right. Your professional image just got even better. No more showing up in rideshares. You arrive in your own vehicle, tools in the trunk, ready to work.</p>
	<p>Your business has gone from informal day labor to a legitimate professional service. The car is the final piece.</p>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="success-box">
	<p style="color: green;"><strong>Success:</strong> You own a car outright and have established a premium direct-service business. Your transportation costs will drop while you keep full control of your schedule.</p>
</div>

